'''Firegems''' (also known as '''fire-gems''')<ref name="Galactic Campaign Guide">''[[Galactic Campaign Guide]]''</ref> were extremely radiant gemstones that had a high price on the black market. Thus, they were an excellent opportunity for profit for many [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]].

Buyers of firegems included the [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] smugglers [[Dubrak Qennto]], [[Jorj Car'das]], and [[Maris Ferasi]], who owned the smuggling ship ''[[Bargain Hunter]]''. While smuggling firegems on the fringes of the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]], they were chased by [[Progga]] the Hutt's ship. However, a frontier picket force of the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy's]] [[Chiss Expansionary Defense Force|Expansionary Fleet]] under [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Mitth'raw'nuruodo]] intercepted them and destroyed Progga's ship, before impounding the ''Hunter'' and detaining its crew.<ref name="Outbound Flight">[[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']]</ref>

==Dangers==
The molecular structure of the firegem vibrated constantly, creating a heat source that made the gems feel warm to the touch. Criminal and terrorist organizations discovered that the vibration of the firegem had an adverse reaction when placed near a hyperdrive reactor, causing the reactor to explode when the ship entered hyperspace. For this reason, they were outlawed by the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]] as well as the [[New Order/Legends|New Order]].

